  "data": {
    "title": "Bubble.io Tips: Best Ways to Build Real Apps Without Code",
    "excerpt": "Discover the best Bubble.io tips to build full web apps without writing code. Logic, databases, and UI — all visual. Start free and launch faster.",
    "featured_image": {
      "$media": {
        "url": "https://tonyciencia.com/blog/bubble-tips.jpg",
        "alt": "Bubble.io Tips: Best Ways to Build Real Apps Without Code",
        "filename": "bubble-tips.jpg"
      }
    },
    "content": [
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "*Disclosure: This post contains affiliate links. If you sign up through them, I may earn a commission at no extra cost to you.*",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l0",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://tonyciencia.com/en/posts/what-is-bubble"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "I built my first SaaS prototype on a Saturday afternoon. No terminal. No frameworks. No begging a developer friend for favors. Just ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Bubble",
            "marks": [
              "l0"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": ", a browser, and a clear idea of what I wanted.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "If you've ever sketched an app on a napkin and thought \"this would take me months to build,\" Bubble changes that equation entirely. It's a no-code platform where you design interfaces visually, wire up logic with workflows, and connect a real database — all without touching a single line of code. And it's not a toy. Companies have raised millions on products built entirely on Bubble.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Here are the tips and best approaches I've gathered after helping multiple teams ship on this platform.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "---",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "1. Start With the Data Model, Not the Interface",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "This is the single biggest mistake new Bubble users make. They jump straight into the drag-and-drop editor and start building beautiful pages. Then they hit a wall when the app needs to actually *do* something.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Before you touch the design tab, open the Data tab and map out your data types. Think about:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "What entities does your app manage?",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " Users, products, orders, projects, messages — whatever fits your use case.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "What fields does each entity need?",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " Name, email, status, price, images, yes/no flags.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "How do they relate to each other?",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " A \"Post\" belongs to a \"User.\" An \"Order\" contains multiple \"Products.\" A \"Task\" is assigned to a \"Team Member.\"",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Bubble's database is relational and visual. You create data types and fields right in the editor, and Bubble handles the backend infrastructure automatically. When your data model is solid, building the UI on top of it becomes straightforward.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Pro tip: Use [option sets] for static data like dropdown categories, status labels, or role types. They load instantly and never hit the database, which keeps your app fast.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l1",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://bubble.pxf.io/c/6249333/1241519/15270"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Ready to explore the platform yourself? ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Create your free Bubble account here",
            "marks": [
              "l1"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " and follow along with these tips.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "---",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "2. Master Workflows — They're the Real Power",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Bubble's visual editor gets all the attention, but workflows are where the magic lives. Every interaction in your app — every button click, every form submission, every automated action — is powered by a workflow.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Here's how to think about them:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Workflows are event-driven.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " You define a trigger (\"When Button Sign Up is clicked\") and then chain a sequence of actions (\"Sign the user up,\" \"Create a new thing in the database,\" \"Navigate to the dashboard,\" \"Send a welcome email\").",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "You can add conditions to any action.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " Want to only send an email if the user's plan is Pro? Add a \"Only when\" condition to that specific step.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Backend workflows run on the server.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " Use them for heavy processing, scheduled tasks (\"Every Monday at 9 AM, send a summary email\"), and API workflows that external services can call.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "One pattern I use constantly: ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "the \"Do a search for\" action inside a workflow",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " to dynamically fetch data and make decisions. For example, check if a user already has a free trial record before creating a new one. It's clean, visual, and eliminates the need for complex backend code.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l2",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://tonyciencia.com/en/posts/how-to-use-bubble"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "If you want a complete walkthrough, check out our ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "step-by-step Bubble tutorial",
            "marks": [
              "l2"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": ".",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "---",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "3. Use Reusable Elements and Build a Component System",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "I see experienced Bubble developers do this, and it saves enormous amounts of time: they treat their Bubble project like a design system.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Instead of rebuilding the same header, card layout, or modal for every page, you create ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "reusable elements",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": ". These are components you define once and drop anywhere. When you update the reusable element, every instance across your app updates automatically.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Here's a starter list of what to make reusable:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Navbar / Header",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " with user profile dropdown and navigation links",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Card components",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " for listings, products, or dashboard widgets",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Modal popups",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " for forms, confirmations, and detail views",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Footer",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " with links and legal text",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Input groups",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " (label + field + validation message) that you use repeatedly",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Bubble also recently introduced a ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "component library",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " in the editor, giving you pre-built UI blocks to accelerate setup. You drag them in, customize the styling, and connect your data. No starting from scratch.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Building this way keeps your app consistent and makes future changes painless. It's the difference between maintaining 3 files and maintaining 300.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "---",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "4. Keep Your App Fast: Performance Tips That Matter",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Bubble apps can be fast. Slow Bubble apps are almost always a result of how they're built, not the platform itself. Here's what actually moves the needle on performance:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Optimize your searches",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Avoid \"Do a search for\" inside repeating groups with too broad of a filter. Be specific. Add constraints early so Bubble fetches less data.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Use \":first item\" or \":count\" instead of loading entire lists when you only need one record or a number.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Limit page load elements",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Don't put 15 repeating groups on a single page. If a section isn't visible by default (it's inside a collapsed group or a tab the user hasn't clicked), set it to \"This element is visible on page load: No.\" Bubble won't fetch its data until it's needed.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Use backend workflows for heavy lifting",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Sending emails, processing data, generating reports — all of this should run as backend workflows, not on the page. This keeps the UI responsive.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Leverage Bubble's built-in CDN",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Static assets like images and files are served through a content delivery network automatically. Use it. Upload images at the right resolution instead of serving 4MB photos that get squeezed into 200px thumbnails.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l3",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://tonyciencia.com/en/posts/why-choose-bubble"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "These aren't theoretical optimizations. I've seen apps go from 8-second load times to under 2 seconds by applying just the first two tips. For a deeper dive, read our guide on ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "why to choose Bubble for your next project",
            "marks": [
              "l3"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": ".",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "---",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "5. Connect Everything With the API Connector",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Bubble plays well with the rest of the internet. Its built-in ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "API Connector",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " plugin lets you connect to virtually any third-party service that has an API — Stripe, OpenAI, SendGrid, Airtable, Notion, you name it.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "The workflow is simple:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "1. Install the API Connector plugin (it's free and built by Bubble).",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "2. Define your API calls: set the endpoint URL, method (GET, POST, etc.), headers, and parameters.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "3. Call those APIs from any workflow or use them as a data source in your UI.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "I've used this to pull live data from financial APIs into dashboards, trigger SMS notifications via Twilio, and even integrate AI-generated content directly into a content management app. The flexibility is remarkable.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Bubble also supports ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "webhooks",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": ", so external services can push data *into* your Bubble app in real time. When a payment succeeds on Stripe? Trigger a workflow in Bubble. When a form is submitted on your marketing site? Push the lead straight into your Bubble CRM.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "And if APIs aren't your thing yet, Bubble's plugin marketplace has thousands of pre-built integrations. Drag, configure, done.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l4",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://tonyciencia.com/en/posts/how-to-use-clickup"
          },
          {
            "_key": "l5",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://tonyciencia.com/en/posts/how-to-use-monday-com"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Want to see how Bubble fits into your workflow alongside tools like project management or outreach? Explore our articles on ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "using ClickUp",
            "marks": [
